1. Julia's `clean_column` function can be written as follows:
```julia
function clean_column(col)
    # Lowercase the column name
    col = lowercase(col);
    # Strip leading and trailing whitespaces
    col = strip(col);
    # Replace any spaces or hyphens with an underscore
    col = replace(col, " " => "_");
    col = replace(col, "-" => "_");
    return col;
end
```
This function takes a column name as input and returns the cleaned version of it. It performs three operations:

1. Converts the column name to lowercase using the `lowercase` function.
2. Strips leading and trailing whitespaces from the column name using the `strip` function.
3. Replaces all occurrences of spaces and hyphens with an underscore using the `replace` function.
